&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION SUMMARY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Head of Quality is a senior leadership position responsible for establishing, implementing, and maturing all quality management functions across Atropos Group&#39;s development and production operations. This role is the company&#39;s primary quality authority and will serve as the central driver of the Production Approval process — leading the quality system infrastructure, processes, and organizational readiness required to achieve an FAA Production Certificate (PC). The Head of Quality will build and lead a high-performing quality organization from the ground up, shaping the culture, systems, and procedures necessary to support production certification activities, entry into service, and long-term operational excellence in a highly regulated aerospace environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FAA Production Certification &amp;amp; Regulatory Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the company&#39;s primary quality authority and key point of contact for all FAA Production Certificate (PC) activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead development, implementation, and continuous improvement of the Quality Management System (QMS) to satisfy FAA PC requirements under 14 CFR Part 21&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate directly with FAA personnel and Designated Airworthiness Representatives (DARs) throughout the PC application and approval process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the Production Approval Holder (PAH) quality manual, quality procedures, and associated command media in support of PC issuance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Type Certificate (TC) activities by ensuring that design-to-production traceability, conformity inspections, and first article evaluations are executed in compliance with FAA requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and interpret applicable FAA regulations, policy updates, and airworthiness directives for impact on quality processes and production readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead internal and external quality audits in support of FAA oversight, including responses to findings and implementation of corrective actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Management System (QMS) Development &amp;amp; Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and implement a scalable, AS9100D-aligned QMS that supports both current development activities and future high-rate production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain the full suite of quality procedures, work instructions, and forms constituting the company&#39;s quality command media structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive QMS integration across all functional areas including engineering, manufacturing, supply chain, and program management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain Quality plans for all major programs, ensuring appropriate inspection, verification, and validation gates are defined and executed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the internal audit program, including scheduling, execution, corrective action tracking, and management review inputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and monitor quality KPIs and metrics to provide leadership with visibility into system health and performance trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead periodic Management Review processes and provide executive leadership with quality system status reports and improvement recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure seamless integration between the QMS and the company’s Safety Management System (SMS), establishing clear interfaces between quality processes and the four SMS components defined under 14 CFR Part 5 (Safety Policy, Safety Risk Management, Safety Assurance, and Safety Promotion)&lt;/li&gt;
